### Legacy note
# This repository no longer uses HTTP request samples as the main usage flow.
# Phone Server is now a local-first Android app.
#
# The intended user flow is:
# 1. Install and open the app.
# 2. Grant local permissions if needed.
# 3. Create a workspace.
# 4. Run shell commands locally on the phone.
# 5. Start and control long-running local services from the Services tab.
#
# There is no required registration, login, device enrollment, or external
# control plane in the current target architecture.
#
# The old Spring Boot API prototype under `src/main/java/com/phoneserver/controlplane`
# remains in the repository only as legacy reference.
